Description: Sherd of body of large North Ionian black-figured pottery dinos; inside reserved; exterior traces of two friezes divided by a band; surface almost wholly worn; another sherd was once attached, as ample remains of shellac testify.
Curator's comments: Probably from same vessel as 1888,0601.393a and c-h
Bibliographic references: Gardner 1888 / Naukratis II (p. 65, no. 784, pl. XXI, no. 784)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 685, no. 435)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.1116)
